"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005817","Department for Education","false","2018-11-15","<p>We have protected the base rate of funding for 16 to 19 year olds for all types of providers until the end of the current spending review period in 2020. We are actively exploring the efficiency and resilience of post-16 education and will be assessing how far existing and forecast funding and regulatory structures enable high quality provision. As with other areas of departmental spending, 16 to 19 funding from 2020 onwards will be considered as part of the next Spending Review.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005817/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T10:21:13.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005817/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005817/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-11-12","Sixth Form Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of increasing the national funding rate for sixth form students.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","190408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005818","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-15","<p>The Ministry of Defence has not made any assessment of the effect of burn pits used by the US to dispose of military waste on the health of members of the UK Armed Forces who served in Iraq and Afghanistan. Where burn pits are used on military operations the UK regularly monitors air quality levels.</p><p>If Serving personnel consider that their health has been affected they should seek medical advice from Joint Medical Group, previously Defence Medical Services. For veterans, their healthcare is provided by the National Health Service in England and the Devolved Administrations. Individuals who believe that they are ill as a result of their service are able to claim compensation through the War Pensions Scheme for the period up to 6 April 2005 and Armed Forces Compensation Scheme for illnesses and injuries on or after 6 April 2005</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005818/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T15:34:48.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005818/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005818/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-12","Armed Forces: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effect of burn pits used to dispose of military waste on the health of people who served in the British armed forces in Iraq and Afghanistan.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","190543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005819","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-15","<p>My ministerial team and I have had numerous discussions with the steel sector – both as part of wider discussions and on this subject alone – since the measures were announced by the US. We and our colleagues across Government have regularly raised this issue directly with the US to make our objections clear. We have also been working closely with the EU to ensure that proportionate action is taken so that UK workers are safeguarded. We remain in regular contact with the EU and the US Administration to try to reach a positive outcome. Together with BEIS officials, I will continue to engage the UK steel and aluminium companies affected by these tariffs to provide advice and support.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005819/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T14:52:02.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005819/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005819/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-11-12","Iron and Steel: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, What discussions he has had with steel companies on the effect of US steel tariffs on the UK steel sector.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","190544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005820","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-15","<p>On current operations, armed forces personnel receive briefings, including health guidance, at all stages of an operational deployment. This includes pre-deployment, on arrival in theatre during Reception Staging and Onward Integration and during decompression. Written guidance is also provided at unit level.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005820/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T15:34:02.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005820/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005820/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-12","Iraq Conflict: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what health guidance was issued to armed forces personnel who were exposed to military burn pits during their service in the 2003 Iraq War.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","190545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005821","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-15","<p>Any Armed Forces veteran who believes they have suffered ill health due to their Service is eligible to claim compensation under the War Pensions Scheme (WPS) or the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS). The WPS covers illness or injury due to Service before 6 April 2005 and the AFCS covers illnesses and injuries on or after 6 April 2005. Both schemes carry full rights of appeal to an independent tribunal.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005821/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T15:32:59.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005821/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005821/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-12","Armed Forces: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what support his Department provides to former armed forces personnel who have health concerns relating to their exposure to military burn pits during the wars in Iraq and Afghanistan.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","190546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005822","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-15","<p>At the Department’s request, Andrew Haines (Network Rail CEO) led industry in reviewing plans for the December 2018 timetable in light of the disruption seen in May 2018. The rail industry advised reductions in the scale of the planned changes for the December 2018 timetable, specifically to reduce the risk of disruption for passengers.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the rail industry has put in place additional assurance processes to test that plans for delivery of the timetable are robust and the Secretary of State has received on-going assurance from industry leaders on its readiness for the implementation of timetable change on 09 December 2018.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005822/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T11:33:06.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005822/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005822/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-12","Railways: Timetables","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he has taken to ensure that (a) the rail industry is ready for the timetable changes due to be implemented on 9 December 2018 and (b) those changes will be delivered without adverse effects on passengers.","false","Biography information for Mohammad Yasin","Bedford","Mohammad Yasin","190547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005823","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-20","<p>As per my previous answer of 24 October 2018 to Question 180166, the pilot will continue in its current form for the 2018/19 training year.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005823/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-20T16:06:59.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005823/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005823/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-12","Shipping: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 24 October 2018 to Question 180166 on Shipping: training, whether the three-year pilot of the ratings training option has been extended; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","190442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005824","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-20","<p>There are 45 UK-owned roll-on roll-off ferries on the UK register, and zero on the other Red Ensign registers (non-UK).</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005824/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-20T11:01:13.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005824/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005824/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-12","Roll-on Roll-off Ships: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 6 November 2018 to Question 185578 on Ferries: Registration, how many roll-on roll-off ferries on the (a) UK and (b) Red Ensign registers are UK-owned.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","190443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005825","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-20","<p>In terms of roll-on roll-off ferries registered in:</p><p>(a) The UK, the Regulations require all registered seagoing vessels to hold a Safe Manning Document issued by the Maritime and Coastguard Agency (MCA). This document specifies the minimum crewing/manning levels. All vessels must be adequately manned for their safe operation, with due regard for the nature of their operation and their location.</p><p> </p><p>The MCA ensures that all roll-on roll-off ferries are correctly and safely manned from a combination of factors determined by the safe manning levels needed to deal with any potential emergency on that vessel as required by the relevant international regulations. The preparedness of the crew is tested by means of a physical drill witnessed by MCA Marine Surveyors<strong>. </strong></p><p> </p><p>(b) The non-UK Red Ensign registers, the MCA is not directly responsible for agreeing the safe crewing levels. Responsibility and obligation under the international conventions have been extended to the Governments of the UK Overseas Territories and Crown Dependencies. As part of the UK Flag State, they are required to follow the same levels and policy as per the UK requirements.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005825/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-20T10:56:32.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005825/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005825/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-11-12","Roll-on Roll-off Ships: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the written answer of 6 November 2018 to Question 185578 on Ferries: Registration, what the Maritime and Coastguard Agency-agreed safe crewing level is on each roll-on roll-off ferry on the (a) UK and (b) Red Ensign registers.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","190444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005826","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-15","<p>As with the vast majority of NHS services, the funding and commissioning of palliative and end of life care, is a local matter, over which individual National Health Service commissioners have responsibility. Local commissioners are best placed to understand the needs of local populations and commission services to meet those needs accordingly.</p><p> </p><p>As part of the £20.5 billion a year for the NHS, NHS England is working with the Department to develop a long-term plan, details of which will be published later this year. End of life care is an important part of the proposals and NHS England will continue working with key stakeholders to test the plan before its publication.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005826/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T16:11:16.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005826/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005826/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-11-12","Palliative Care: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether the Government plans to increase funding for end-of-life care; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","190548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005827","Department for Education","false","2018-11-20","<p>Ofsted has a duty to consider pupils’ behaviour and safety as part of its section 5 school inspections. While it is not Ofsted’s role to investigate individual cases, inspectors always look at exclusions on school inspections and ask head teachers about trends and reasons for exclusions. The issue of exclusion is also covered as part of the joint Ofsted/Care Quality Commission inspections of local authorities’ effectiveness in identifying and meeting the needs of children and young people who have special educational needs or disabilities. Inspectors will report on overall levels of exclusions, and may comment when there is a specific or recurring trend.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005827/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-20T16:05:31.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005827/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005827/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-11-12","Pupil Exclusions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what powers Ofsted has to investigate the (a) level of and (b) reason for school exclusions through its (i) school inspections and (ii) joint area inspections with the Care Quality Commission.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","190480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005828","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-15","<p>I refer the Hon Member to my answer to Question UIN 176245 on 11 October 2018.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005828/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T09:33:47.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005828/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005828/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-11-12","Social Rented Housing: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that the social housing system supports people with mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","190549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005829","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-15","<p>It is the long standing position of the Government not to comment on individual immigration issues.</p><p>Asia Bibi’s acquittal will be very welcome news to her family and those who have campaigned in Pakistan and around the world for her release. The UK continues to follow developments on this case very closely.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005829/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-15T14:15:14.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005829/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005829/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-11-12","Asia Bibi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with (a) the Home Secretary and (b) his counterpart in Pakistan on offering asylum in the UK to Asia Bibi and her family.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","190550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005830","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-19","<p>On 16 December 2015, it was announced that a change would be made to the War Pension Scheme legislation to enable the payment, on or after 11 April 2016, of a lump sum to veterans diagnosed with diffuse mesothelioma.</p><p> </p><p>The number of veterans who have been awarded a War Disablement Pension for mesothelioma is:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>11 April 2016 to 31 March 2017</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2017 to 31 March 2018</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2018 to 13 November 2018</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The number of veterans who have been awarded a lump sum payment for mesothelioma under the War Pension Scheme:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>11 April 2016 to 31 March 2017</p></td><td><p>119</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2017 to 31 March 2018</p></td><td><p>85</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2018 to 13 November 2018</p></td><td><p>38</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>There have been no compensation claims made by Service personnel for mesothelioma.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005830/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-19T16:46:59.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005830/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005830/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-12","Armed Forces: Mesothelioma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) service personnel and (b) veterans have been awarded (i) a War Disablement Pension and (ii) lump sum compensation for mesothelioma in each year since December 2015.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","190551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005831","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-20","<p>The information requested is not held. The Armed Forces Credit Union, &quot;Joining Forces&quot;, is operated by three Credit Unions independent of the Ministry of Defence.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005831/answer",,,,,"190554","2018-11-20T15:05:57.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005831/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005831/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-12","Armed Forces: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much money was loaned to (a) service personnel and (b) veterans through the Armed Forces Credit Union between (i) October 2015 and October 2017 and (ii) October 2017 and October 2018.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","190552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005832","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-20","<p>The table below shows the number of Service personnel and veterans who have deductions from payroll or pensions for savings and loans through the Armed Forces Credit Union since November 2015, when it became possible to do so. The facility for veterans to have deductions taken from pension payments has only been available since 2016.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>2018</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Service personnel</p></td><td><p>240</p></td><td><p>1,220</p></td><td><p>3,120</p></td><td><p>4,590</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Veterans</p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Yearly Total</p></td><td><p>240</p></td><td><p>1,224</p></td><td><p>3,129</p></td><td><p>4,599</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Please note the 2018 data is provided up to 31 October 2018, and individuals may have deductions taken in more than one year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005832/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-20T15:08:03.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005832/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1005832/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-11-12","Armed Forces: Loans and Personal Savings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) service personnel and (b) veterans have received payroll and pension deductions for the purposes of savings and loans in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","190553"
